org.jimmutable.core.fields

Class FieldMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this map
    V - the type of mapped values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>, Field
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FieldConcurrentHashMap, FieldHashMap, FieldTreeMap

    public abstract class FieldMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Map<K,V>, Field
    An implementation of a Collection that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable). In other words, a wrapper for a Collection that implements Field.

    This class is designed to be extended. Most of the collection hierarchy is already wrapped as part of the standard jimmutable library, but further extensions should go quickly as the base class does nearly all of the work. However, extension implementors should take time to carefully understand the immutability principles involved and to write careful unit tests to make sure that the implementations are as strictly immutable as possible. Null keys and/or values are not allowed (attempts to put either will result in no action being taken)

    Author:
    Jim Kane
